### Describe the problem

To establish reactivity for a passed prop within a context, we need to create a store variable that mirrors the prop's updates:

### Parent
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import Child from './Child.svelte';
	import Grandchild from './Grandchild.svelte';

	let disabled: boolean = false;
</script>

<button on:click={() => (disabled = !disabled)}>toggle</button>
<Child {disabled}><Grandchild /></Child>
```

### Child
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import { setContext } from 'svelte';
	import { writable, type Writable } from 'svelte/store';

	export let disabled: boolean;

	let disabledStore: Writable<boolean> = writable(disabled);
	$: disabledStore.set(disabled);

	setContext('child', disabledStore);
</script>

<slot />
```

### Grandchild
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import type { Writable } from 'svelte/store';
	import { getContext } from 'svelte';

	let disabledStore: Writable<boolean> = getContext('child');
</script>

<p>{$disabledStore}</p>
```

### Describe the proposed solution

Using the passed prop directly in this manner would be quite convenient:

### Parent
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import Child from './Child.svelte';
	import Grandchild from './Grandchild.svelte';

	let disabled: boolean = false;
</script>

<button on:click={() => (disabled = !disabled)}>toggle</button>
<Child {disabled}><Grandchild /></Child>
```

### Child
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import { setContext } from 'svelte';
	import { writable, type Writable } from 'svelte/store';

	export let disabled: boolean;

	$: setContext('child', disabled);
</script>

<slot />
```

### Grandchild
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import type { Writable } from 'svelte/store';
	import { getContext } from 'svelte';

	$: disabled = getContext<boolean>('child');
</script>

<p>{disabled}</p>
```

### Alternatives considered

The problem contains the solution. Yet, implementing this proposed solution might necessitate additional code. This alternative could involve making Svelte's context fully reactive, which might eliminate the need for extra code and it should not introduce any breaking changes.

### Importance

