### Describe the bug

During the creation and running of the transition animations, the DOM is read from and written to. As this happens in sequence for each element in an `#each` block, this causes style recalculation and layout over and over.

Interestingly this does *not* happen in Firefox.


### Reproduction

```svelte
<script>
	import { scale } from 'svelte/transition';
	const count = 1000;
	let show = false;
</script>

<button on:click={() => show = !show}>Toggle</button>

{#each { length: count } as i}
	{#if show}
		<div transition:scale={{duration: 300}}>Item</div>
	{/if}
{/each}
```

[REPL](https://svelte.dev/repl/20038d15b718426d972412d824151d7b?version=3.50.1)

---

I tried splitting the transition code into two phases: Create animations & run animations

```patch
  add_render_callback(() => {
  	if (!div_transition) div_transition = create_bidirectional_transition(div, scale, { duration: 300 }, true);
-  	div_transition.run(1);
+  	queueMicrotask(() => div_transition.run(1));
